Acknowledgements

Joyride Studio is a visual authoring helper built on top of react-joyride
(https://github.com/gilbarbara/react-joyride). React-joyride does the heavy
lifting at runtime — it is the tour engine, this project is a wrapper around
it that adds a capture inspector, a Settings panel, and design-system-aware
defaults. Without react-joyride, none of this would work.

Joyride Studio is an independent open-source project. It is not affiliated
with, endorsed by, or sponsored by react-joyride or its maintainers. The
copyright in react-joyride belongs to its own authors, and react-joyride is
itself MIT-licensed; its license text is reproduced below in full as required
by the MIT terms and as a thank-you to Gil Barbara and the react-joyride
contributors.

If you are looking for the canonical, lower-level way to build guided tours
in React, please use react-joyride directly. Joyride Studio is one possible
authoring workflow on top of it — not a replacement, not a fork, not a
competitor.

